# Build-time HTTP ingest for universal-dev-logging (inlined by esbuild → main.ts).
#
# `npm run build` and `npm run dev` run `scripts/ensure-ink-debug-ingest-before-build.mjs` first.
# It writes this file with:
# - `INK_DEBUG_CURSOR_INGEST_URL` — `http://127.0.0.1:7662/ingest/…` for desktop / `adb reverse`
# - `INK_DEBUG_INGEST_PATH` — `/ingest/…` only (from Cursor debug log or defaults)
# - `INK_DEBUG_LAN_IPV4` — this machine’s LAN IPv4 (auto; Obsidian **mobile** POSTs here over Wi‑Fi)
#
# Discovery order: shell INK_DEBUG_CURSOR_INGEST_URL → `.cursor/cursor-debug-ingest-url` →
# newest `.cursor/debug-*.log` (`httpIngestPath`) → preserve existing non-loopback `.env` vs loopback log
# → defaults. See `scripts/ink-debug-ingest-env-lib.mjs`.
#
# Optional: `INK_DEBUG_SKIP_AUTO_INGEST=1` skips updating this file before build.
# Optional (ensure script / CI): `INK_DEBUG_SKIP_LAN_DISCOVERY=1` leaves `INK_DEBUG_LAN_IPV4` empty.
# Optional (shell only, `ensure-…` before build): `INK_DEBUG_SKIP_DEBUG_LOG_PRUNE=1`; `INK_DEBUG_DEBUG_LOG_PRUNE_KEEP=10`.
# Manual: `npm run sync-ink-debug-ingest -- "http://…"`.
# See: eink-bridge/docs/implementations/debug-logging.md
INK_DEBUG_CURSOR_INGEST_URL=
INK_DEBUG_INGEST_PATH=
INK_DEBUG_LAN_IPV4=
